      • addFile

        public ProjectResultReport addFile(FormDataMultiPart body,
                                   String executionId,
                                   Boolean async)
                            throws ApiException
        Posts a file for the specified test run Use this operation to send additional files required by the executed test recipes. For example, you may need to send an Excel file for your test recipe that uses an Excel data source. The test recipe will be in the \"PENDING\" status until it receives the required file. Use the <code>multipart/form-data</code> media type for this request.
        Parameters:
        body - Required file as `form-data`. (required)
        executionId - The id of the test run that waits for the files. [See how you can get it](http://readyapi.smartbear.com/testserver/tutorials/your_first_recipe/results). (required)
        async - Specifies when the TestServer replies:<br/>`true` - Immediately.<br/>`false` - After the execution is over. (optional, default to true)
        Returns:
        ProjectResultReport
        Throws:
        ApiException - if fails to make API call

      • cancelExecution

        public void cancelExecution(String executionID)
                     throws ApiException
        Cancels the specified recipe execution Use this operation to stop the run specified by <i>executionID</i>. You can find in the response to your execution request ([see how](http://readyapi.smartbear.com/testserver/tutorials/your_first_recipe/results)), or you can send a GET <code>/readyapi/executions</code> request to the TestServer.
        Parameters:
        executionID - The id of the test run to stop. (required)
        Throws:
        ApiException - if fails to make API call

        Parameters:

        Throws:

      • getMessageExchanges

        public HarLogRoot getMessageExchanges(String executionID)
                               throws ApiException
        Returns the transaction logs for the specified recipe execution. Use this operation to get transaction logs (individual request and recponse of execited test steps) on the recipe execution specified by <i>executionID</i>. You can find in the response to your execution request ([see how](http://readyapi.smartbear.com/testserver/tutorials/your_first_recipe/results)), or you can send a GET <code>/readyapi/executions/{executionID}/logs</code> request to the TestServer.
        Parameters:
        executionID - The id of the desired test run. (required)
        Returns:
        HarLogRoot
        Throws:
        ApiException - if fails to make API call

      • postProjectExecution

        public ProjectResultReport postProjectExecution(InputStream body,
                                                String testCaseName,
                                                String testSuiteName,
                                                Boolean async,
                                                String callback)
                                         throws ApiException
        Executes a Ready! API test project. Use this operation to send a Ready! API test project to the TestServer. You command the TestServer to execute the entire project, or an individual test suite or test case in it. The recipe request should have a Ready! API project file (.xml) attached to it.
        Parameters:
        body - Ready! API XML project. (optional)
        testCaseName - The name of the test case to run. (optional)
        testSuiteName - The name of the test suite to run. (optional)
        async - Specifies when TestServer replies:<br/>`true` - Immediately.<br/>`false` - After the execution is over. (optional, default to true)
        callback - The URL, to which the results will be posted. (optional)
        Returns:
        ProjectResultReport
        Throws:
        ApiException - if fails to make API call
